The paper deals with the problem of computing edit distance to a context-free grammar, specifically the Dyck language. This falls under the category of formal languages (cs.FL) and algorithms for parsing and grammar analysis (cs.DM). The algorithmic techniques used involve data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). Additionally, the paper discusses applications in natural language processing and memory checking, which could potentially fall under machine learning (cs.LG).
